article.headline: Charleston Southern 120, Toccoa Falls 43
article.story: CHARLESTON, S.C. -- Zimmy Nwogbo came off the bench to score 14 points and grab 10 rebounds, one of six scorers in double figures for Charleston Southern in its 120-43 victory over Toccoa Falls on Tuesday night. Kelvin Martin also scored 14 for the Buccaneers (4-4), who got their most points since a 136-52 victory over Allen in December of 1992. Fellow starters Sheldon Strickland contributed 13 points and Jeremy Sexton 12. Thomas Odom added 11 points and Chris Grier 10 for a Charleston Southern bench that put up 66 points. Fourteen players scored for the Buccaneers. Johnny Sutherland scored 13 points to lead the Eagles (2-6) of the National Christian College Athletic Association. Charleston Southern, which opened the game with a 17-2 run, shot 59.3 percent (51 of 86) to 26.3 percent (15 of 57) for Toccoa Falls and outrebounded the Eagles 57-21.
